WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:02.100 --> 00:00:03.300
MALE SPEAKER: Good afternoon,
everyone.

00:00:03.300 --> 00:00:04.750
Thanks a lot for coming out.

00:00:04.750 --> 00:00:08.130
It is my great pleasure to
welcome Prasad Kaipa to

00:00:08.130 --> 00:00:09.420
Authors at Google.

00:00:09.420 --> 00:00:12.755
He's here today to talk about
his book, "From Smart to

00:00:12.755 --> 00:00:13.350
Wise."

00:00:13.350 --> 00:00:16.480
And it's actually a great
honor to have him.

00:00:16.480 --> 00:00:21.700
Dr. Kaipa is an executive coach,
mentor, author, and

00:00:21.700 --> 00:00:24.930
founder of the Center for
Leadership, Innovation, and

00:00:24.930 --> 00:00:27.180
Change at the Union School
of Business.

00:00:27.180 --> 00:00:35.670
He is also a long-time part
of Silicon Valley.

00:00:35.670 --> 00:00:36.620
He has presented.

00:00:36.620 --> 00:00:40.850
He has led executive
development, career-coaching,

00:00:40.850 --> 00:00:42.840
everything at multiple different
companies here at

00:00:42.840 --> 00:00:44.010
Silicon Valley.

00:00:44.010 --> 00:00:47.610
And it's an honor to welcome
him to Google today.

00:00:47.610 --> 00:00:50.523
So if we could please all give
him a big round of applause.

00:00:50.523 --> 00:00:52.988
[APPLAUSE]

00:00:52.988 --> 00:00:54.238
PRASAD KAIPA: Thank you.

00:00:57.930 --> 00:00:59.180
Good afternoon.

00:01:01.830 --> 00:01:08.590
I think what today we'll talk
about is to look at why the

00:01:08.590 --> 00:01:11.710
smartness is the baseline now.

00:01:11.710 --> 00:01:15.540
It is no longer something that
gives us the privilege.

00:01:15.540 --> 00:01:19.890
When I was growing up in India,
when I went to IIT,

00:01:19.890 --> 00:01:22.130
that was something very,
very special.

00:01:22.130 --> 00:01:26.020
Or when I worked for Apple
Computer in the '80s, that was

00:01:26.020 --> 00:01:27.810
something very special.

00:01:27.810 --> 00:01:31.110
But coming and giving
a talk at Google,

00:01:31.110 --> 00:01:32.660
everybody is very special.

00:01:32.660 --> 00:01:34.500
Otherwise, they wouldn't
be here.

00:01:34.500 --> 00:01:38.260
So from that aspect, it's
like a baseline.

00:01:38.260 --> 00:01:43.400
If the smartness is the new
baseline at Google, and many

00:01:43.400 --> 00:01:46.800
of the Silicon Valley companies
at this moment, how

00:01:46.800 --> 00:01:48.360
would you stay one step ahead?

00:01:48.360 --> 00:01:51.250
How do you demonstrate
personal leadership?

00:01:51.250 --> 00:01:55.310
That is the theme which
I address a lot more.

00:01:55.310 --> 00:01:59.820
So next step I thought I should
look at is, how many of

00:01:59.820 --> 00:02:03.430
you think you are smart?

00:02:03.430 --> 00:02:06.240
Other people may feel that
you are smart or not.

00:02:06.240 --> 00:02:10.840
But from your own perspective,
would you raise your hands if

00:02:10.840 --> 00:02:13.760
you think you are smart?

00:02:13.760 --> 00:02:17.380
It's an interesting scenario,
because depending on different

00:02:17.380 --> 00:02:20.950
cultural context and norms,
everybody has their own

00:02:20.950 --> 00:02:23.920
expectations and standards
of whether to raise

00:02:23.920 --> 00:02:24.920
their hands or not.

00:02:24.920 --> 00:02:28.130
Can you keep it up
for one minute.

00:02:28.130 --> 00:02:29.530
OK, great.

00:02:29.530 --> 00:02:32.290
So some of you didn't
raise the hands.

00:02:32.290 --> 00:02:36.170
I won't exactly ask at this
moment why, but let

00:02:36.170 --> 00:02:37.920
me get to the next.

00:02:37.920 --> 00:02:39.785
Can you raise your hand if
you think you are wise?

00:02:44.870 --> 00:02:45.310
Yeah?

00:02:45.310 --> 00:02:47.140
Could be sometimes
[INAUDIBLE].

00:02:47.140 --> 00:02:48.580
Interesting.

00:02:48.580 --> 00:02:53.210
So definitely smaller number
of hands than smartness,

00:02:53.210 --> 00:02:54.330
number one.

00:02:54.330 --> 00:02:57.310
Number two, they
went up slowly.

00:02:57.310 --> 00:03:00.330
Maybe we associate smartness
with speed,

00:03:00.330 --> 00:03:01.970
and wisdom with slowness.

00:03:01.970 --> 00:03:04.250
That's a frame pattern
which we'll talk a

00:03:04.250 --> 00:03:05.560
little bit more about.

00:03:05.560 --> 00:03:07.650
I was curious about that.

00:03:07.650 --> 00:03:10.920
Next thing, have you read the
book "From Smart to Wise,"

00:03:10.920 --> 00:03:11.540
which I have written?

00:03:11.540 --> 00:03:13.050
Any of you?

00:03:13.050 --> 00:03:14.400
Have you done--

00:03:14.400 --> 00:03:17.360
there is a baseline assessment
which we came up with, which

00:03:17.360 --> 00:03:22.070
is a five-minute assessment
on FromSmarttoWise.com.

00:03:22.070 --> 00:03:26.640
If you go, there are 18
questions, because you have

00:03:26.640 --> 00:03:27.920
not read the book.

00:03:27.920 --> 00:03:30.900
Of course, there is also a link
to that to [INAUDIBLE]

00:03:30.900 --> 00:03:32.440
to assessment.

00:03:32.440 --> 00:03:33.640
You can go there.

00:03:33.640 --> 00:03:37.500
I recommend, before you start
the book, if you can actually

00:03:37.500 --> 00:03:40.040
do that assessment, then
read the book and

00:03:40.040 --> 00:03:41.390
start applying it.

00:03:41.390 --> 00:03:45.500
That may, actually the value of
what you need will become a

00:03:45.500 --> 00:03:48.520
lot more applicable, and
a lot more grounded in

00:03:48.520 --> 00:03:50.680
what you want to do.

00:03:50.680 --> 00:03:52.840
So let me start with
a definition.

00:03:52.840 --> 00:03:55.570
Because the smartness is the new
currency in the knowledge

00:03:55.570 --> 00:03:59.480
age, how do you really
define it?

00:03:59.480 --> 00:04:02.870
We defined it in the book,
smartness is the application

00:04:02.870 --> 00:04:07.330
of intelligence for
self interest.

00:04:07.330 --> 00:04:12.120
So practical smartness is about
using your knowledge to

00:04:12.120 --> 00:04:17.120
get ahead, using your knowledge
to become a leader

00:04:17.120 --> 00:04:19.890
when other people are not having
the same opportunity,

00:04:19.890 --> 00:04:24.350
or to make money, to get
a job, to move ahead--

00:04:24.350 --> 00:04:25.580
different ways.

00:04:25.580 --> 00:04:28.960
It's all connected with, how
do you make sure your

00:04:28.960 --> 00:04:33.000
smartness based off your own
growth and development?

00:04:33.000 --> 00:04:37.000
That's traditional, simpler
way to define it.

00:04:37.000 --> 00:04:40.260
But of course, smartness is
not just about people.

00:04:40.260 --> 00:04:44.110
It is actually something that
is pervading our culture.

00:04:44.110 --> 00:04:49.040
For example, this IBM has been
calling this decade as the

00:04:49.040 --> 00:04:51.030
decade of smartness.

00:04:51.030 --> 00:04:54.330
They're trying to create what
you might call a smarter

00:04:54.330 --> 00:05:00.230
planet, and how do we really
begin to use our smartness for

00:05:00.230 --> 00:05:04.820
the larger context of
environment, population,

00:05:04.820 --> 00:05:08.220
technology, to work
for everybody?

00:05:08.220 --> 00:05:11.930
And of course, I don't have to
talk at Google about the

00:05:11.930 --> 00:05:13.690
smartphones.

00:05:13.690 --> 00:05:15.716
If you notice, I put
the iPhone all

00:05:15.716 --> 00:05:19.060
the way in the back.

00:05:19.060 --> 00:05:23.420
The other thing is the
smart televisions.

00:05:23.420 --> 00:05:25.400
It is not just the
smart television

00:05:25.400 --> 00:05:26.930
that is becoming popular.

00:05:26.930 --> 00:05:29.270
You are also talking
about smart meters

00:05:29.270 --> 00:05:30.540
of different kind.

00:05:30.540 --> 00:05:33.670
In California, P&amp;G--

00:05:33.670 --> 00:05:35.330
actually, it's PG&amp;E--

00:05:35.330 --> 00:05:40.070
introduced smart meters, and
of course, Nest smart

00:05:40.070 --> 00:05:41.680
temperature control.

00:05:41.680 --> 00:05:44.360
Not just one unit,
one appliance.

00:05:44.360 --> 00:05:48.660
Now, everybody talks about an
entire house, an entire

00:05:48.660 --> 00:05:51.590
community is becoming smarter.

00:05:51.590 --> 00:05:56.420
Because of this pervasiveness
of smartness as the new

00:05:56.420 --> 00:06:01.550
currency, I wonder whether the
smartness is a new definition

00:06:01.550 --> 00:06:02.820
for dumbness.

00:06:02.820 --> 00:06:08.430
Because if you try to really
look at everybody being smart,

00:06:08.430 --> 00:06:12.110
you have to focus on something
other than smartness if you

00:06:12.110 --> 00:06:14.140
need to get ahead.

00:06:14.140 --> 00:06:20.460
So in that context, sometimes
holding back on self-interest,

00:06:20.460 --> 00:06:25.500
holding back on being too smart
actually could be wise.

00:06:25.500 --> 00:06:31.320
At some level, reflecting,
introspecting, slowing down to

00:06:31.320 --> 00:06:34.670
make sure that you have actually
paid attention to the

00:06:34.670 --> 00:06:39.050
context of value, and taking
care of people on your team,

00:06:39.050 --> 00:06:41.450
taking care of your organization
not just to a

00:06:41.450 --> 00:06:44.660
self-interest, could be
considered not just

00:06:44.660 --> 00:06:47.330
smart, but also wise.

00:06:47.330 --> 00:06:51.540
In fact, when I used to work
with several entrepreneurs and

00:06:51.540 --> 00:06:55.030
the venture capital firms in
the Valley, they talked

00:06:55.030 --> 00:07:00.440
generally about if an idea has
a 70% chance of success to

00:07:00.440 --> 00:07:04.890
make it as an entrepreneurial
success, they say don't do it.

00:07:04.890 --> 00:07:05.830
Why?

00:07:05.830 --> 00:07:09.280
Everybody in the Valley would be
focusing on something that

00:07:09.280 --> 00:07:11.250
has a 70% chance of success.

00:07:11.250 --> 00:07:15.160
So that means on the ground,
your entrepreneurial company,

00:07:15.160 --> 00:07:19.980
based on that idea, may
not actually fly.

00:07:19.980 --> 00:07:24.850
If you reverse it, if an idea
has only 30% chance of

00:07:24.850 --> 00:07:28.800
success, but if you can really
put attention to it--

00:07:28.800 --> 00:07:31.630
because not many other
entrepreneurs are also

00:07:31.630 --> 00:07:33.520
interested in that idea--

00:07:33.520 --> 00:07:37.190
you have a 70% chance of success
for making the company

00:07:37.190 --> 00:07:38.540
successful.

00:07:38.540 --> 00:07:44.190
So what I'm trying to raise is
it is counter-intuitive for

00:07:44.190 --> 00:07:48.710
people to be successful in
the age of knowledge.

00:07:48.710 --> 00:07:53.190
You have to think outside the
box of, what is in it for me?

00:07:53.190 --> 00:07:56.220
How can I be successful
in the short-term?

00:07:56.220 --> 00:08:00.770
You may have to be expand your
circle of not only influence,

00:08:00.770 --> 00:08:04.070
your circle of interest to
include your team, your

00:08:04.070 --> 00:08:07.900
organization, sometimes your
community, and bring in the

00:08:07.900 --> 00:08:11.840
context of noble purpose, if
you want to be successful,

00:08:11.840 --> 00:08:14.890
with your smartness.

00:08:14.890 --> 00:08:17.900
Interestingly, somebody says--

00:08:17.900 --> 00:08:19.800
like, of course, William
Shakespeare

00:08:19.800 --> 00:08:21.510
puts it quite nicely.

00:08:21.510 --> 00:08:25.730
"A fool thinks of himself to be
wise, but a wise man always

00:08:25.730 --> 00:08:30.630
knows himself to be a fool
first." So at some level, we

00:08:30.630 --> 00:08:34.640
are trying to say, smartness
doesn't cut it to be

00:08:34.640 --> 00:08:38.080
successful, let alone in Silicon
Valley, because of

00:08:38.080 --> 00:08:42.360
complexity that we live in,
the ambiguity [INAUDIBLE].

00:08:42.360 --> 00:08:46.250
Nobody can tell you exactly
what to do, how to do it.

00:08:46.250 --> 00:08:49.600
And especially, when Larry comes
up and says, we need to

00:08:49.600 --> 00:08:53.780
have it as a 10x, you need
to do 10x thinking.

00:08:53.780 --> 00:08:57.940
In Google, it is no longer
sufficient for you to look at,

00:08:57.940 --> 00:09:00.160
how do I make incremental
improvement?

00:09:00.160 --> 00:09:03.680
If I need to create a
breakthrough innovation, and

00:09:03.680 --> 00:09:08.180
if my products and solutions are
always online, even a few

00:09:08.180 --> 00:09:13.730
minutes of going out could have
significant headlines,

00:09:13.730 --> 00:09:16.820
saying that Google is out for a
few minutes, three, minutes,

00:09:16.820 --> 00:09:18.360
two minutes.

00:09:18.360 --> 00:09:21.080
In that type of a context, you
have to figure out a way to

00:09:21.080 --> 00:09:22.760
say how to be wise.

00:09:22.760 --> 00:09:28.050
But becoming wise has got
a lot of connotations.

00:09:28.050 --> 00:09:32.130
In the earlier stage, when my
co-author, Navi, and myself,

00:09:32.130 --> 00:09:36.010
when we started writing a book,
one gentlemen whom we

00:09:36.010 --> 00:09:39.080
were interviewing, he asked us,
do you think you are wise

00:09:39.080 --> 00:09:41.350
enough to write the book?

00:09:41.350 --> 00:09:44.460
If not, why are you
writing it?

00:09:44.460 --> 00:09:47.490
If you are not wise, what gives
you the authority to

00:09:47.490 --> 00:09:49.920
talk about wisdom?

00:09:49.920 --> 00:09:54.410
That's a very legitimate
question, because everybody in

00:09:54.410 --> 00:09:58.610
different cultures have their
own opinions about what it

00:09:58.610 --> 00:10:01.130
means to be wise.

00:10:01.130 --> 00:10:05.150
Of course, I thought I'll give
some practical examples,

00:10:05.150 --> 00:10:07.990
collaborating with the
myths that we have.

00:10:07.990 --> 00:10:11.040
People say once you are wise,
you will stay wise.

00:10:11.040 --> 00:10:15.490
This gentleman was
head of IMF.

00:10:15.490 --> 00:10:19.840
He was pretty much a shoo-in
for the President of France

00:10:19.840 --> 00:10:23.440
till he couldn't keep
his clothes on.

00:10:23.440 --> 00:10:26.110
Sometimes, nobody talks
about how to use

00:10:26.110 --> 00:10:28.300
your wisdom or smartness.

00:10:28.300 --> 00:10:30.820
But unfortunately, latest--

00:10:30.820 --> 00:10:31.920
what you call--

00:10:31.920 --> 00:10:35.940
records say that he's being
charged with all kinds of

00:10:35.940 --> 00:10:39.830
charges, which are so demeaning
to what could've

00:10:39.830 --> 00:10:44.270
been an IMF president or
a President of France.

00:10:44.270 --> 00:10:49.050
So once you are wise, you
cannot stay wise.

00:10:49.050 --> 00:10:55.950
This is a grounded, pragmatic,
action-oriented scenario where

00:10:55.950 --> 00:11:00.130
every day, you need to take some
steps to ask yourself,

00:11:00.130 --> 00:11:02.940
this is a smart approach,
this is a wise approach.

00:11:02.940 --> 00:11:06.330
Can I make a wiser decision
today for is?

00:11:06.330 --> 00:11:08.660
Can I take a wiser
action today?

00:11:08.660 --> 00:11:12.470
That's the only way you can
continue to keep updating on

00:11:12.470 --> 00:11:14.280
your wisdom.

00:11:14.280 --> 00:11:20.120
The second myth says that age
and maturity make people wise.

00:11:20.120 --> 00:11:23.410
General Petraeus was celebrated
general in

00:11:23.410 --> 00:11:24.595
Afghanistan.

00:11:24.595 --> 00:11:27.440
He was the director of CIA.

00:11:27.440 --> 00:11:32.980
But I wonder what happens when
it comes to thinking when you

00:11:32.980 --> 00:11:38.720
are doing the largest spy
organization in the world, but

00:11:38.720 --> 00:11:43.360
you think some of the stuff that
you do can stay private?

00:11:43.360 --> 00:11:45.530
Sometimes, I just don't know.

00:11:45.530 --> 00:11:49.240
And of course, we have
the latest hero.

00:11:49.240 --> 00:11:52.710
He thinks about what it is,
and there was a nice comic

00:11:52.710 --> 00:11:55.590
about a couple of weeks ago.

00:11:55.590 --> 00:11:59.080
So if you think that the only
chosen few have access to

00:11:59.080 --> 00:12:03.310
wisdom, without a question, what
kind of a wisdom is that?

00:12:03.310 --> 00:12:08.490
So I wonder whether the wisdom
is actually a birth rite when

00:12:08.490 --> 00:12:09.650
we are young.

00:12:09.650 --> 00:12:14.160
If you have children, you do
know, some of the common sense

00:12:14.160 --> 00:12:18.130
questions that the children
raise, some of that kind of

00:12:18.130 --> 00:12:21.770
comments they make, some of the
honesty and authenticity

00:12:21.770 --> 00:12:23.170
children have--

00:12:23.170 --> 00:12:26.670
I wonder whether we beat it
out of their system in the

00:12:26.670 --> 00:12:30.390
name of socializing, in the
name of politeness, in the

00:12:30.390 --> 00:12:34.580
name of what you call emotional
intelligence, in the

00:12:34.580 --> 00:12:36.480
name of everything else.

00:12:36.480 --> 00:12:42.050
I wonder we try to focus them
more on trying to be smart,

00:12:42.050 --> 00:12:47.250
according to all standards, but
let go of the common sense

00:12:47.250 --> 00:12:51.630
wisdom that would give them the
larger perspective, little

00:12:51.630 --> 00:12:55.630
bit more broader way of
looking at the world.

00:12:55.630 --> 00:12:59.200
Now let me get it closer
to the home.

00:12:59.200 --> 00:13:01.490
If you take some of
these people--

00:13:01.490 --> 00:13:05.440
many people I asked, when I give
talks around the world,

00:13:05.440 --> 00:13:07.710
would you call them smart?

00:13:07.710 --> 00:13:10.040
Lots of hands went up.

00:13:10.040 --> 00:13:11.830
Would you call them wise?

00:13:11.830 --> 00:13:14.310
Not many hands went up.

00:13:14.310 --> 00:13:15.700
Why is that?

00:13:15.700 --> 00:13:19.240
Do we associate wisdom
with age?

00:13:19.240 --> 00:13:24.300
Do we assume that only old
people with a lot of gray hair

00:13:24.300 --> 00:13:29.090
have to be wise, but if you're
young, you cannot be wise?

00:13:29.090 --> 00:13:34.770
Interestingly, we talk to one
of the analysts who used to

00:13:34.770 --> 00:13:39.710
work with this gentlemen,
Mark Zuckerberg,

00:13:39.710 --> 00:13:40.770
in the early stage.

00:13:40.770 --> 00:13:45.970
She said when he came to her
research firm talking about

00:13:45.970 --> 00:13:50.820
social network, she was not
at all convinced about his

00:13:50.820 --> 00:13:53.510
smartness, let alone
his wisdom.

00:13:53.510 --> 00:13:58.460
But a year, year and a half
later, when he came back, she

00:13:58.460 --> 00:14:02.400
almost thought it was a
completely different person.

00:14:02.400 --> 00:14:07.630
She began to realize within the
year time period, he had

00:14:07.630 --> 00:14:11.580
associated himself with a lot
of good advisers, wise

00:14:11.580 --> 00:14:13.930
leaders, and he learned.

00:14:13.930 --> 00:14:16.900
And because of his learning,
he was able to transform

00:14:16.900 --> 00:14:21.080
himself, which is what your
founders seems to have done.

00:14:21.080 --> 00:14:26.400
They started it, brought
somebody else in, and then,

00:14:26.400 --> 00:14:29.170
when the time is right, and
when they felt they were

00:14:29.170 --> 00:14:32.460
mature enough, Larry took
the CEO role again.

00:14:32.460 --> 00:14:37.380
So there is a role in which
there is humility; willingness

00:14:37.380 --> 00:14:40.660
to say, I need to learn from
others; and willingness to

00:14:40.660 --> 00:14:43.130
say, this may not be
the right thing.

00:14:43.130 --> 00:14:45.000
Those are some characteristics--

00:14:45.000 --> 00:14:47.400
it doesn't matter whether
you're a young or old--

00:14:47.400 --> 00:14:49.450
that can come in.

00:14:49.450 --> 00:14:54.300
And finally, if you look at some
of these people, I don't

00:14:54.300 --> 00:14:57.290
think there will be much of
disagreement if we talk about

00:14:57.290 --> 00:14:58.980
their wisdom.

00:14:58.980 --> 00:15:02.770
One thing you might want to
think about is, did they give

00:15:02.770 --> 00:15:05.920
up their smartness to be wise?

00:15:05.920 --> 00:15:10.270
Interestingly, when Navi and I
were looking at the title for

00:15:10.270 --> 00:15:15.410
this book, we wanted to call it
"Smart and Wise." That is

00:15:15.410 --> 00:15:18.610
when the editor told us, you
guys are writing the book, but

00:15:18.610 --> 00:15:21.430
you haven't figured out how to
come up with a wise cycle.

00:15:21.430 --> 00:15:22.540
We said, why?

00:15:22.540 --> 00:15:25.080
He said, if you call it "Smart
and Wise," where is the hook

00:15:25.080 --> 00:15:26.480
in the book.

00:15:26.480 --> 00:15:28.070
Why would anybody buy it?

00:15:28.070 --> 00:15:31.840
You need to have a title by
creating a journey or a

00:15:31.840 --> 00:15:37.250
pathway from smart to wise so
that people get some doubt.

00:15:37.250 --> 00:15:40.200
Maybe their smartness is not
good enough, they'll buy it.

00:15:40.200 --> 00:15:44.390
So they said, first, it is going
to talk about wisdom,

00:15:44.390 --> 00:15:46.700
but you have to be smart in the
beginning to come up with

00:15:46.700 --> 00:15:48.000
the right title.

00:15:48.000 --> 00:15:49.890
So we are learning that
some of these

00:15:49.890 --> 00:15:52.060
are extremely important.

00:15:52.060 --> 00:15:55.960
But of course, finally, it is
also important to recognize

00:15:55.960 --> 00:16:00.820
wisdom is not about coming up
with answers, but it is about

00:16:00.820 --> 00:16:03.060
asking the right questions.

00:16:03.060 --> 00:16:05.480
Considering the kind of what
do you do-- whether it is

00:16:05.480 --> 00:16:08.280
YouTube, whether it is Google,
whether it is many of the

00:16:08.280 --> 00:16:09.740
other things--

00:16:09.740 --> 00:16:14.790
your innovation, especially
breakthrough innovation, will

00:16:14.790 --> 00:16:19.640
come not by incrementally
tinkering what you already

00:16:19.640 --> 00:16:24.590
have, but being able to ask
difficult questions, recognize

00:16:24.590 --> 00:16:27.730
your products are online
all the time.

00:16:27.730 --> 00:16:30.670
And if you have to make changes,
sometimes you may

00:16:30.670 --> 00:16:35.990
have to fail bigger before you
can succeed even bigger.

00:16:35.990 --> 00:16:39.130
When you don't have the courage,
when you don't have

00:16:39.130 --> 00:16:43.150
the wherewithal, and when you
don't go for the 10x as you

00:16:43.150 --> 00:16:48.000
are talking about, the ability
to stay afloat--

00:16:48.000 --> 00:16:51.790
let alone the ability to grow
and become bigger and bigger--

00:16:51.790 --> 00:16:53.230
is going to be questionable.

00:16:53.230 --> 00:16:57.300
But of course, we can talk from
a Google perspective, but

00:16:57.300 --> 00:17:01.280
the key it comes down to is
Google is nothing but all of

00:17:01.280 --> 00:17:04.210
you, and a few more out there.

00:17:04.210 --> 00:17:09.270
That means each one of us have
to take responsibility for

00:17:09.270 --> 00:17:13.740
what I'm doing, how will it make
a difference to my team,

00:17:13.740 --> 00:17:15.970
my division, my company?

00:17:15.970 --> 00:17:20.280
If I can have that larger
perspective, when what you do

00:17:20.280 --> 00:17:23.510
becomes successful, you also
become successful with it.

00:17:23.510 --> 00:17:27.150
In the book, I call it
enlightened self-interest.

00:17:27.150 --> 00:17:31.210
That means if you want to be a
personal leader, if you want

00:17:31.210 --> 00:17:35.290
to be extraordinary and be
recognized for what you do,

00:17:35.290 --> 00:17:40.280
you have to think about how we
expand that pie, like a game.

00:17:40.280 --> 00:17:43.040
Being in Silicon Valley, we'll
use another metaphor, right?

00:17:43.040 --> 00:17:45.240
I'm sure you're all
familiar with it.

00:17:45.240 --> 00:17:48.830
Many times, when smart people
get together to create an

00:17:48.830 --> 00:17:51.860
entrepreneurial company, they
talk about, what is your

00:17:51.860 --> 00:17:54.820
share, what is my share,
what is the investor

00:17:54.820 --> 00:17:56.740
share, and all of them?

00:17:56.740 --> 00:17:58.710
One gentlemen taught me.

00:17:58.710 --> 00:18:01.750
He said, when you're coaching
these people, you need to help

00:18:01.750 --> 00:18:02.870
them to see--

00:18:02.870 --> 00:18:06.670
even if you have 70%
of the grape--

00:18:06.670 --> 00:18:11.660
70% share of a small company
doesn't mean very much.

00:18:11.660 --> 00:18:16.250
Your job as entrepreneurial
team is to make that grape

00:18:16.250 --> 00:18:18.140
into a watermelon.

00:18:18.140 --> 00:18:22.270
When you make the grape into
orange or a watermelon, even

00:18:22.270 --> 00:18:27.030
at 5% stake in that watermelon
is going to be many, many,

00:18:27.030 --> 00:18:29.380
many times larger
than the grape.

00:18:29.380 --> 00:18:34.010
So that means being smart is
looking at what share do I

00:18:34.010 --> 00:18:36.470
have, how much stock
do I have?

00:18:36.470 --> 00:18:42.040
Being wise means, how can each
of us work together to make

00:18:42.040 --> 00:18:44.762
whatever we have into
much bigger?

00:18:44.762 --> 00:18:48.710
It shifts the perspective
significantly.

00:18:48.710 --> 00:18:51.530
But that doesn't always
come true properly.

00:18:51.530 --> 00:18:55.805
Let me give an example of
Microsoft, for example.

00:18:55.805 --> 00:18:59.500
In 1999, the Department
of Justice

00:18:59.500 --> 00:19:02.420
wanted to break up Microsoft.

00:19:02.420 --> 00:19:08.640
And Bill Gates' testimony didn't
go very well, and got a

00:19:08.640 --> 00:19:11.400
bad rep for the Microsoft.

00:19:11.400 --> 00:19:13.300
Bill Gates stepped down.

00:19:13.300 --> 00:19:16.880
He wanted to go ahead and create
the Gates Foundation.

00:19:16.880 --> 00:19:20.950
Of course, since then, he has
given away $26 billion, and

00:19:20.950 --> 00:19:23.830
went ahead and started
doing something.

00:19:23.830 --> 00:19:27.880
And now, he has become, from
a smart Bill Gates, he has

00:19:27.880 --> 00:19:29.600
become a wise Bill Gates.

00:19:29.600 --> 00:19:34.380
But on the other hand,
he left the Microsoft

00:19:34.380 --> 00:19:36.180
to the smart Ballmer.

00:19:36.180 --> 00:19:39.110
Just to give some of
his wise quotes.

00:19:39.110 --> 00:19:41.720
You might have heard
of some of this.

00:19:41.720 --> 00:19:44.780
"There is no chance that the
iPhone is going to get any

00:19:44.780 --> 00:19:46.890
significant market share.

00:19:46.890 --> 00:19:50.350
No chance." You can see this
on YouTube, by the way.

00:19:50.350 --> 00:19:53.650
"Linux is a cancer that the
attaches itself to an

00:19:53.650 --> 00:19:57.420
intellectual property sense to
everything it touches." And

00:19:57.420 --> 00:20:00.490
this is the classic--

00:20:00.490 --> 00:20:02.410
"Google is not a real company.

00:20:02.410 --> 00:20:05.940
It's a house of cards."
Very interesting.

00:20:05.940 --> 00:20:10.000
And of course, Bill Gates
himself wrote a book on future

00:20:10.000 --> 00:20:13.330
of technology called "Road
Ahead." It didn't have any

00:20:13.330 --> 00:20:16.010
mention of internet,
by the way.

00:20:16.010 --> 00:20:22.140
So sometimes, I wonder there are
more limits to smartness

00:20:22.140 --> 00:20:24.690
than we pay attention to.

00:20:24.690 --> 00:20:28.630
The key to remember about
smartness is today, you may be

00:20:28.630 --> 00:20:32.660
the smartest person in the room,
but tomorrow there are

00:20:32.660 --> 00:20:34.020
no guarantees.

00:20:34.020 --> 00:20:36.430
Somebody else will come and
take your position.

00:20:36.430 --> 00:20:38.750
So it's a moving target.

00:20:38.750 --> 00:20:42.100
You can't actually try
to outsmart people

00:20:42.100 --> 00:20:43.560
on a constant basis.

00:20:43.560 --> 00:20:47.560
It's exhausting, and
it is not worth it.

00:20:47.560 --> 00:20:48.600
Second--

00:20:48.600 --> 00:20:53.000
smartness is always about either
a vision of the future,

00:20:53.000 --> 00:20:55.390
or what you have done
in the past.

00:20:55.390 --> 00:20:57.920
Not worth it, because it
doesn't give you the

00:20:57.920 --> 00:21:01.920
mindfulness of [INAUDIBLE]
in the present moment.

00:21:01.920 --> 00:21:03.520
Third--

00:21:03.520 --> 00:21:07.610
what is smart from one
perspective may be foolish

00:21:07.610 --> 00:21:11.150
from another, and it doesn't
translate very well to one

00:21:11.150 --> 00:21:12.720
culture to another.

00:21:12.720 --> 00:21:16.440
You may have to really begin
to think about, maybe

00:21:16.440 --> 00:21:20.520
smartness is not the only way
to be successful, and

00:21:20.520 --> 00:21:24.640
recognize that knowing and
seeing the patterns ahead of

00:21:24.640 --> 00:21:28.880
everybody else is a trap,
because it leads to ultimately

00:21:28.880 --> 00:21:31.390
self-denial, because you--

00:21:31.390 --> 00:21:35.520
I came up with a phrase called
core incompetence.

00:21:35.520 --> 00:21:39.640
Your signature strength of
yesterday that got you to this

00:21:39.640 --> 00:21:44.240
job today is nailing your foot,
and prevents you from

00:21:44.240 --> 00:21:45.990
going somewhere else.

00:21:45.990 --> 00:21:48.050
So where is your foot
nailed to the

00:21:48.050 --> 00:21:52.730
floor is in your smartness.

00:21:52.730 --> 00:21:57.960
So watch out, and make sure
smartness is not an addiction

00:21:57.960 --> 00:22:02.650
that you keep feeding, because
unless you recontextualize it

00:22:02.650 --> 00:22:07.180
as wisdom, your personal
leadership does not get

00:22:07.180 --> 00:22:10.700
recognized as much as you want
it to be recognized.

00:22:10.700 --> 00:22:13.150
So what is this wise
leadership?

00:22:13.150 --> 00:22:15.100
How do you really
recontextualize

00:22:15.100 --> 00:22:17.350
smartness into wisdom?

00:22:17.350 --> 00:22:21.530
I believe the smartness
is like a pendulum--

00:22:21.530 --> 00:22:24.470
it swings to two extremes.

00:22:24.470 --> 00:22:28.860
One extreme, if it swings, I
call it a business smartness,

00:22:28.860 --> 00:22:31.750
like an entrepreneurial
smartness.

00:22:31.750 --> 00:22:36.590
The other extreme, what you
call swings, I call it a

00:22:36.590 --> 00:22:38.160
functional smartness.

00:22:38.160 --> 00:22:42.000
That means I want to be the head
of my staff, I want to be

00:22:42.000 --> 00:22:47.270
the chief technologist, I want
to be the CEO, even Nobel

00:22:47.270 --> 00:22:51.130
Laureate I had a good to
interview several Nobel

00:22:51.130 --> 00:22:53.060
Laureate over a period
of time.

00:22:53.060 --> 00:22:57.240
I found out even they get
stuck in one end of the

00:22:57.240 --> 00:23:00.150
spectrum or other end
of the spectrum.

00:23:00.150 --> 00:23:04.670
The wise leadership is anchoring
the wisdom to your

00:23:04.670 --> 00:23:06.220
larger purpose.

00:23:06.220 --> 00:23:10.600
when you anchor your smartness
with something larger as

00:23:10.600 --> 00:23:14.150
wisdom, then you can swing
from one end to other end

00:23:14.150 --> 00:23:16.920
without the loss of face,
because you're no longer

00:23:16.920 --> 00:23:20.000
committed to the questions, or
becoming an expert in the

00:23:20.000 --> 00:23:22.220
room, but you're willing
to look stupid.

00:23:22.220 --> 00:23:24.260
You're willing to ask
dumb questions.

00:23:24.260 --> 00:23:27.450
You're willing to ask some
things which other people are

00:23:27.450 --> 00:23:30.560
not raising, like emperor
has no clothes.

00:23:30.560 --> 00:23:33.420
Because of that, you may be able
to find something very

00:23:33.420 --> 00:23:34.620
interesting.

00:23:34.620 --> 00:23:39.280
Arno Penzias, one of the Nobel
Laureates, talks about how he

00:23:39.280 --> 00:23:42.730
actually ended up getting
a Nobel Prize.

00:23:42.730 --> 00:23:48.360
He said once, he was driving
from New Jersey through the

00:23:48.360 --> 00:23:52.470
Midwest with his wife and a
nine-year-old daughter.

00:23:52.470 --> 00:23:55.020
And who was telling it seems--

00:23:55.020 --> 00:23:58.090
why is that when you change
from one radio station to

00:23:58.090 --> 00:24:01.540
another radio station,
you have this buzz?

00:24:01.540 --> 00:24:03.700
How can you not prevent
this buzz?

00:24:03.700 --> 00:24:05.980
You are the physicist,
what can you do?

00:24:05.980 --> 00:24:07.450
And where is this coming from?

00:24:07.450 --> 00:24:10.620
He said, oh, this is an
electronic noise.

00:24:10.620 --> 00:24:14.880
But later, he realized he
doesn't know where the noise

00:24:14.880 --> 00:24:18.540
is coming when you are going
from one station to another,

00:24:18.540 --> 00:24:20.160
and he spent some time.

00:24:20.160 --> 00:24:24.340
He realized, it is an
intergalactic cosmic noise,

00:24:24.340 --> 00:24:26.810
which got him a Nobel
Prize for that.

00:24:26.810 --> 00:24:32.220
So sometimes, it is extremely
important that smartness gets

00:24:32.220 --> 00:24:36.470
us focused on knowledge
and what we know.

00:24:36.470 --> 00:24:41.180
But if you want to do 10x
contribution to you or to your

00:24:41.180 --> 00:24:45.320
company, you may have ask more
questions, and more questions

00:24:45.320 --> 00:24:48.260
for which you have no
clue how to answer.

00:24:48.260 --> 00:24:52.230
Then, the ambiguity you have,
the stress that you are

00:24:52.230 --> 00:24:55.880
dealing with, and the complexity
of work that we

00:24:55.880 --> 00:25:00.320
deal with, that can be leveraged
to gain more wisdom,

00:25:00.320 --> 00:25:04.770
instead of proving yourself
to be more smart.

00:25:04.770 --> 00:25:08.530
So let me summarize a couple of
things, and I'll give you a

00:25:08.530 --> 00:25:10.610
few examples.

00:25:10.610 --> 00:25:12.910
Ultimately, leadership--

00:25:12.910 --> 00:25:16.770
whether you manage other
people or not--

00:25:16.770 --> 00:25:20.190
to be a leader, to be a personal
leader, it all comes

00:25:20.190 --> 00:25:22.290
down to three things.

00:25:22.290 --> 00:25:23.920
How do you make decisions?

00:25:23.920 --> 00:25:26.230
Do you use judgment and

00:25:26.230 --> 00:25:29.180
discernment in making decisions?

00:25:29.180 --> 00:25:32.170
Second, how do you
take actions?

00:25:32.170 --> 00:25:38.150
Are those actions towards your
own benefit, or with an

00:25:38.150 --> 00:25:41.760
enlightened self-interest that
benefits your team, your

00:25:41.760 --> 00:25:44.470
family, or your organization?

00:25:44.470 --> 00:25:47.520
Third, how do you communicate?

00:25:47.520 --> 00:25:50.940
Do you communicate saying,
what I talk, I take

00:25:50.940 --> 00:25:53.930
responsibility; what you
listen, I have no

00:25:53.930 --> 00:25:54.950
responsibility?

00:25:54.950 --> 00:25:57.110
That's one way to communicate.

00:25:57.110 --> 00:26:01.980
Another one is to look at and
say what I communicate is

00:26:01.980 --> 00:26:04.560
based on what you
have received.

00:26:04.560 --> 00:26:08.870
It doesn't mean I have to talk
a lot, but maybe much of what

00:26:08.870 --> 00:26:11.410
I have to do in communication--

00:26:11.410 --> 00:26:15.260
maybe listening, maybe asking
questions, reading your body

00:26:15.260 --> 00:26:18.770
language, using a lot more
emotional intelligence,

00:26:18.770 --> 00:26:20.850
context sensitivity--

00:26:20.850 --> 00:26:23.500
all of this become extremely
important.

00:26:23.500 --> 00:26:26.220
Especially when we are smart,
it becomes a lot

00:26:26.220 --> 00:26:27.990
harder to do this.

00:26:27.990 --> 00:26:30.790
So wise leadership--

00:26:30.790 --> 00:26:35.910
we define it as same
intelligence application, but

00:26:35.910 --> 00:26:39.060
this time, we ask you
to do two things.

00:26:39.060 --> 00:26:43.670
One is reflection on the
context around you.

00:26:43.670 --> 00:26:48.090
Second, introspection on the
skills that you bring.

00:26:48.090 --> 00:26:55.090
If you can couple reflection and
introspection, and focus

00:26:55.090 --> 00:26:56.700
on the larger good--

00:26:56.700 --> 00:27:01.520
that larger good could extend
as far as you want it to be.

00:27:01.520 --> 00:27:05.365
For Steve Jobs, larger
good extended only up

00:27:05.365 --> 00:27:08.140
to he and his company.

00:27:08.140 --> 00:27:11.410
But for you, you need
to make a choice.

00:27:11.410 --> 00:27:15.550
How much good is larger
good for you?

00:27:15.550 --> 00:27:19.840
In other words, it is
repurposing your intelligence

00:27:19.840 --> 00:27:23.010
and smart leadership in
the present moment.

00:27:23.010 --> 00:27:26.780
It is about being mindful, not
just about the past or the

00:27:26.780 --> 00:27:31.470
future, but it is about being
here and now at some level.

00:27:31.470 --> 00:27:33.770
What does wise leadership
get you?

00:27:33.770 --> 00:27:38.270
It gets you ethical clarity
in times of complexity.

00:27:38.270 --> 00:27:44.070
Second, judgment when you
need discernment.

00:27:44.070 --> 00:27:48.320
And finally, humility,
recognizing I might have come

00:27:48.320 --> 00:27:51.770
up with a great solution today,
but it has happened

00:27:51.770 --> 00:27:53.750
because of help with
other people.

00:27:53.750 --> 00:27:56.960
And when you honor other people,
when you respect other

00:27:56.960 --> 00:28:02.230
people who help you, chances
are that can become a

00:28:02.230 --> 00:28:04.440
sustainable relationship.

00:28:04.440 --> 00:28:09.310
So let me just give a court,
and ask whether

00:28:09.310 --> 00:28:10.650
you have any questions.

00:28:10.650 --> 00:28:14.180
And I can give examples of wise
leadership, and I can do

00:28:14.180 --> 00:28:15.560
a lot of different things.

00:28:15.560 --> 00:28:18.080
But for you to become wise,
there are three

00:28:18.080 --> 00:28:19.760
most important stuff.

00:28:19.760 --> 00:28:23.850
As I said, reflection is
a very powerful tool.

00:28:23.850 --> 00:28:26.890
Second, we call it politically
correct word--

00:28:26.890 --> 00:28:28.390
best practices.

00:28:28.390 --> 00:28:31.570
We try to look at the
best practices.

00:28:31.570 --> 00:28:34.980
In my book, we wrote a lot of
examples based on interviews

00:28:34.980 --> 00:28:38.430
and narratives of various
successful leaders, which is

00:28:38.430 --> 00:28:40.120
the easiest.

00:28:40.120 --> 00:28:43.090
Third, experience.

00:28:43.090 --> 00:28:47.950
What I recommend is once you
complete this talk, actually

00:28:47.950 --> 00:28:51.190
think about-- when
you go back--

00:28:51.190 --> 00:28:52.500
three areas.

00:28:52.500 --> 00:28:56.840
What do I need to communicate
in my project?

00:28:56.840 --> 00:29:00.390
What decisions do I need to make
to take the next step?

00:29:00.390 --> 00:29:03.300
What actions are imperative
for me?

00:29:03.300 --> 00:29:07.780
In both of these scenarios, if
you can think every day at

00:29:07.780 --> 00:29:11.780
least one decision, one action,
and one communication.

00:29:11.780 --> 00:29:15.340
Is this a smart one,
or a wise one?

00:29:15.340 --> 00:29:20.510
Can I begin to take one decision
a day that is wiser,

00:29:20.510 --> 00:29:24.410
one action a day that would
move me towards wise

00:29:24.410 --> 00:29:25.250
leadership.

00:29:25.250 --> 00:29:28.660
I have a feeling over
a period of time--

00:29:28.660 --> 00:29:31.130
as somebody said, can I
be wiser sometimes?

00:29:31.130 --> 00:29:32.890
I think you raised
the question.

00:29:32.890 --> 00:29:35.240
I think that is the way
in which we go.

00:29:35.240 --> 00:29:40.300
Even though wisdom may be the
birth rite, because we have

00:29:40.300 --> 00:29:44.360
forgotten and got conditioned,
we may have to unlearn and

00:29:44.360 --> 00:29:47.610
selectively forget what
we have picked

00:29:47.610 --> 00:29:49.590
up, how to be smart.

00:29:49.590 --> 00:29:52.750
And step by step, we can make
progress towards wise

00:29:52.750 --> 00:29:55.210
leadership.

00:29:55.210 --> 00:29:57.330
Let me stops for a minute
and check--

