If you have interest in it, I
have identified a couple of

00:32:29.900 --> 00:32:32.080
suggestions for you.

00:32:32.080 --> 00:32:34.490
Let me know when you
want to implement.

00:32:34.490 --> 00:32:35.990
I will give it to you.

00:32:35.990 --> 00:32:40.370
So what you have done in the
minute, one-minute coaching is

00:32:40.370 --> 00:32:43.880
you have created a context for
other people to ask for the

00:32:43.880 --> 00:32:48.940
feedback, and recognize that you
have given your positive,

00:32:48.940 --> 00:32:54.070
appreciative stance to your
feedback already, and you have

00:32:54.070 --> 00:32:58.100
created a gap for them to
really look at, how do I

00:32:58.100 --> 00:32:59.390
transcend that gap?

00:32:59.390 --> 00:33:02.270
Because they are intentional,
because they are asking for

00:33:02.270 --> 00:33:05.560
it, they will receive your
genuine feedback much more

00:33:05.560 --> 00:33:07.230
appreciatingly, and they become

00:33:07.230 --> 00:33:08.960
friends, and stay friends.

00:33:08.960 --> 00:33:12.930
So that is what I think is the
way in which authenticity is

00:33:12.930 --> 00:33:15.640
not always good.

00:33:15.640 --> 00:33:17.240
You have to watch for it.

00:33:17.240 --> 00:33:21.270
That's what I call wisdom is not
about staying on one end

00:33:21.270 --> 00:33:22.080
or other end.

00:33:22.080 --> 00:33:25.320
It is not right or wrong,
good or bad.

00:33:25.320 --> 00:33:29.640
