00:33:46.710 --> 00:33:50.600
Here is a gentleman, Alan
Mulally I had a good chance to

00:33:50.600 --> 00:33:55.000
interact with in Boeing,
and later, in Ford.

00:33:55.000 --> 00:33:57.150
He comes out of--

00:33:57.150 --> 00:33:59.060
he had aeronautical
background.

00:33:59.060 --> 00:34:03.080
At one time, he wanted
to be an astronaut.

00:34:03.080 --> 00:34:09.400
And unfortunately, because he
has some eye issue, he could

00:34:09.400 --> 00:34:10.500
not become an astronaut.

00:34:10.500 --> 00:34:11.739
He was very disappointed.

00:34:11.739 --> 00:34:15.170
But then he said, you know, at
least let me make the planes.

00:34:15.170 --> 00:34:16.310
So he joined--

00:34:16.310 --> 00:34:19.190
from Kansas, he came
to Seattle.

00:34:19.190 --> 00:34:20.730
He joined Boeing.

00:34:20.730 --> 00:34:24.210
He became the president of
Boeing Commercial Aircraft.

00:34:24.210 --> 00:34:27.900
Somewhere down the line, he was
invited to Ford, and that

00:34:27.900 --> 00:34:30.350
was 2006 time period.

00:34:30.350 --> 00:34:35.920
And then when the financial
malaise hit the nation, most

00:34:35.920 --> 00:34:37.840
of the companies took
the bailout--

00:34:37.840 --> 00:34:40.190
government bailout.

00:34:40.190 --> 00:34:45.010
Instead, Ford went ahead-- and
under the guidance of Alan

00:34:45.010 --> 00:34:48.909
Mulally-- took about
$24 billion loan.

00:34:48.909 --> 00:34:53.139
They actually had to
get that moniker

00:34:53.139 --> 00:34:55.730
mortgaged, that Ford moniker.

00:34:55.730 --> 00:34:59.000
Everybody looked at it and said,
isn't it stupid for you

00:34:59.000 --> 00:35:01.790
to not take the easy money?

00:35:01.790 --> 00:35:03.600
Not only that--

00:35:03.600 --> 00:35:06.940
there so many other actions
which it took, everybody

00:35:06.940 --> 00:35:09.840
questioned, we should have never
brought that person from

00:35:09.840 --> 00:35:11.820
outside the automobile
industry.

00:35:11.820 --> 00:35:13.710
What are some of
those actions?

00:35:13.710 --> 00:35:19.090
He went ahead, and sold the
most expensive, profitable

00:35:19.090 --> 00:35:23.160
Ford businesses, like Land
Rover and Jaguar.

00:35:23.160 --> 00:35:26.230
He sold Indian Tata Group.

00:35:26.230 --> 00:35:32.510
And Ford was making a lot of
money making trucks and SUVs.

00:35:32.510 --> 00:35:36.280
He said, you know, we need to
start focusing on smart cars.

00:35:36.280 --> 00:35:39.440
Ford said, we don't
make money on it.

00:35:39.440 --> 00:35:41.600
Then he said, you better figure
out how to make money

00:35:41.600 --> 00:35:44.660
on the small cars, because
that is the future.

00:35:44.660 --> 00:35:47.130
Then he found out that--

00:35:47.130 --> 00:35:48.430
what you call--

00:35:48.430 --> 00:35:53.700
Ford Taurus, which used to be
a famous car, they shut done

00:35:53.700 --> 00:35:56.830
that brand because they said
nobody is buying it.

00:35:56.830 --> 00:36:01.000
He said, well, if you have
already built a brand value,

00:36:01.000 --> 00:36:04.400
figure out how to come up with
something, and make that brand

00:36:04.400 --> 00:36:06.820
value to pay for itself
instead of trying

00:36:06.820 --> 00:36:08.420
to build a new brand.

00:36:08.420 --> 00:36:13.090
So in more ways than one, he was
very counter-intuitive to

00:36:13.090 --> 00:36:15.560
what they were doing
in and out.

00:36:15.560 --> 00:36:22.770
But now, five years later, Ford
is much, much more green,

00:36:22.770 --> 00:36:27.280
much, much more profitable, and
it is on a path to success

00:36:27.280 --> 00:36:28.620
that was unprecedented.

00:36:28.620 --> 00:36:31.090
And even when compared to their
competitors, they have

00:36:31.090 --> 00:36:32.800
done exceedingly well.

00:36:32.800 --> 00:36:38.080
So in that respect, I believe
certain ways in which Alan

00:36:38.080 --> 00:36:42.800
Mulally had taken decisions,
taken actions, and how he

00:36:42.800 --> 00:36:48.050
communicated are some things
that increase the value of not

00:36:48.050 --> 00:36:51.940
only the Ford brand, but
also his own brand.

00:36:51.940 --> 00:36:55.900
And some of you might want to
check out Alan Mulally videos.

00:36:55.900 --> 00:36:57.170
There are--

00:36:57.170 --> 00:36:59.140
Alan Mulally, some of the
articles about him.

00:36:59.140 --> 00:37:01.260
He is extremely positive.

00:37:01.260 --> 00:37:05.220
When I went to interview him, he
knew more about me, and he

00:37:05.220 --> 00:37:08.120
was really preparing various
stuff for me

00:37:08.120 --> 00:37:09.820
rather than for himself.

00:37:09.820 --> 00:37:10.960
Then when I came out--

00:37:10.960 --> 00:37:12.610
actually, it was at Boeing--

00:37:12.610 --> 00:37:16.310
I asked the secretary, is
Alan always like that?

00:37:16.310 --> 00:37:17.380
He said, yup.

00:37:17.380 --> 00:37:18.850
He's always the cheerleader.

00:37:18.850 --> 00:37:22.800
For anything he takes on, he's
positive, appreciative,

00:37:22.800 --> 00:37:25.680
gung-ho, and 100% into it.

00:37:25.680 --> 00:37:26.670
Interesting.

00:37:26.670 --> 00:37:29.240
But those are some things which
we don't know how to

00:37:29.240 --> 00:37:31.780
deal with sometimes in
different cultures.

00:37:31.780 --> 00:37:35.730
You need to think about, what
is your authentic style, and

00:37:35.730 --> 00:37:37.830
what appropriate style?

00:37:37.830 --> 00:37:41.420
How do you really make it work
in whichever group, whichever

00:37:41.420 --> 00:37:42.670
company you are in.

00:37:44.930 --> 00:37:47.940
Let's look at the context
sensitivity and discernment

00:37:47.940 --> 00:37:49.230
for a minute.

00:37:49.230 --> 00:37:56.620
Sam Palmisano, when he took over
IBM in 2002, he saw the

00:37:56.620 --> 00:37:57.630
writing on the wall--

00:37:57.630 --> 00:38:00.400
PCs are becoming commodities.

00:38:00.400 --> 00:38:03.090
Hardware is not where
the energy is.

00:38:03.090 --> 00:38:04.320
So what did he do?

00:38:04.320 --> 00:38:08.360
He sold the entire PC
business to Lenovo.

00:38:08.360 --> 00:38:10.620
He sold the hard disks
to Hitatchi.

00:38:10.620 --> 00:38:13.540
He got rid of even the
chips manufacturing.

00:38:13.540 --> 00:38:18.720
He completely converted IBM
into services business.

00:38:18.720 --> 00:38:23.020
Few years later, Leo
Apotheker, from

00:38:23.020 --> 00:38:25.170
SAP, took over HP.

00:38:25.170 --> 00:38:27.360
He tried to do the same thing.

00:38:27.360 --> 00:38:29.700
He wanted to get
rid of the HP--

00:38:29.700 --> 00:38:32.880
what you might call the
hardware business.

00:38:32.880 --> 00:38:36.696
Even though they bought the
Palm for $1 billion a year

00:38:36.696 --> 00:38:41.420
ago, within a month of
introducing the Palm Tablet,

00:38:41.420 --> 00:38:44.260
he closed it down.

00:38:44.260 --> 00:38:47.870
Of course, they closed him down
before he had a chance to

00:38:47.870 --> 00:38:52.500
do more of what they called
damage to HP.

00:38:52.500 --> 00:38:57.770
What was smart at one time was
no along wise by the time it

00:38:57.770 --> 00:38:58.950
came to Apotheker.

00:38:58.950 --> 00:39:03.490
That means you cannot just
blindly follow successful

00:39:03.490 --> 00:39:06.810
people, even though they may
be your bosses, they may be

00:39:06.810 --> 00:39:09.000
your seniors, or someone else.

00:39:09.000 --> 00:39:13.440
You will have to pay attention
to what is appropriate, and

00:39:13.440 --> 00:39:19.090
use discernment and judgment
to make it work.

00:39:19.090 --> 00:39:22.840
In India, when I studied,
there was a gentleman.

00:39:22.840 --> 00:39:24.200
This gentleman--

00:39:24.200 --> 00:39:27.690
called Dr. V., for a short
way to think about--

00:39:27.690 --> 00:39:31.190
he created, after he retired
as an eye surgeon

00:39:31.190 --> 00:39:32.970
at the age of 55--

00:39:32.970 --> 00:39:35.490
he said, I'm too young
to retire.

00:39:35.490 --> 00:39:37.990
I want to make a contribution
to the world.

00:39:37.990 --> 00:39:42.250
So he converted his family
housing to an 11-bed hospital.

00:39:42.250 --> 00:39:46.620
And he convinced everybody he
knew in his family and his

00:39:46.620 --> 00:39:51.040
friends to becoming the eye
doctors, or to provide eye

00:39:51.040 --> 00:39:55.110
medicine supplies, or to create
an organization, or to

00:39:55.110 --> 00:39:57.020
create training.

